data.name: infoAuxTag.SuperTooltip
data.value:
Select a pre-existing scenario structure BSP tag to be used by the project's generated scenario tag.

If a scenario structure BSP tag has not already been created for the world mesh, there will be an opportunity to import and process a mesh after the project has been created.

data.name: infoProjectTeam.SuperTooltip
data.value:
List members on the team.

Note that the Team List will be included in the map credits to cite the authors.

The Team List may be updated at any time via the Project Properties pane.

data.name: infoTemplateList.SuperTooltip
data.value:
Select the type of map the project will be.

MP - Multiplayer
SP - Single Player
UI - User Interface

Note that available map types vary by game. The selection list will contain only the map types available for the selected game.

data.name: infoObfuxMap.SuperTooltip
data.value:
Specify if the map will be obfuscated when compiled to help protect the map from being decompiled.

Obfuscation modifies the map in a way that makes it difficult to decompile and steal tags from, while still allowing the game to play the map without any ill effects.

Note that, while obfuscation does offer a measure of protection, it is not absolute protection from decompilation.

data.name: infoProjectAuthor.SuperTooltip
data.value:
Set the project author's name.

Note that this name will be included in the map credits to cite the author.

The Author Name may be updated at any time via the Project Properties pane.

data.name: infoMapFileName.SuperTooltip
data.value:
Customize the file name that will be used for the map file created when the project is compiled.

If no custom file name is specified, the automatically generated file name (displayed in gray) will be used.

The map file name may only contain alphanumeric characters. Spaces are not allowed.
